Package: BioSeqAligner
Type: Package
Title: A DNA sequence alignment, visualization and manipulation tool
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Kashvi Shah
Maintainer: <kashvishah4@gmail.com>
Description: A collection of tools for DNA sequence analysis. This package provides functions for finding motifs, generating dot plots for sequence 
    alignment, computing reverse complements, transcribing DNA to RNA, and calculating GC content. It aims to simplify common tasks in bioinformatics and molecular biology research.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/Code-krafter22/BioSeqAligner
BugReports: https://github.com/Code-krafter22/BioSeqAligner/issues
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    stringi,
    stringr
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
